2.1 AR

Autoregressive Model, AR

\[ X_t = c + \phi_1 X_{t-1} + \phi_2 X_{t-2} + \dots + \phi_p X_{t-p} + \epsilon_t \]

  • \(X_t\) \(t\)
  • \(c\)
  • \(\phi_i\)
  • \(\epsilon_t\)

2.2 MA

Moving Average Model, MA

\[ X_t = \mu + \theta_1 \epsilon_{t-1} + \theta_2 \epsilon_{t-2} + \dots + \theta_q \epsilon_{t-q} + \epsilon_t \]

  • \(\mu\)
  • \(\theta_i\)
  • \(\epsilon_t\)

2.3 ARMA

Autoregressive Moving Average Model, ARMAARMA

\[ X_t = c + \phi_1 X_{t-1} + \dots + \phi_p X_{t-p} + \theta_1 \epsilon_{t-1} + \dots + \theta_q \epsilon_{t-q} + \epsilon_t \]

2.4 ARIMA

Autoregressive Integrated Moving Average Model, ARIMAARMA

\[ \Delta^d X_t = c + \phi_1 \Delta^{d} X_{t-1} + \dots + \theta_q \epsilon_{t-q} + \epsilon_t \]

  • \(\Delta^d\) \(d\)

2.5 ARIMASARIMA

ARIMASeasonal ARIMA, SARIMAARIMA

\[ X_t = ARIMA(p, d, q) \times (P, D, Q)_m \]

  • \((P, D, Q)_m\) \(m\)

library(forecast)
## Registered S3 method overwritten by 'quantmod':
##   method            from
##   as.zoo.data.frame zoo
library(ggplot2)

# AirPassengers
data <- AirPassengers

# 
ggplot(data.frame(time = as.numeric(time(data)), value = as.numeric(data)), aes(x = time, y = value)) +
  geom_line(color = "blue") +
  labs(title = "Monthly Air Passengers", x = "Year", y = "Number of Passengers") +
  theme_minimal()

# ARIMA
model <- auto.arima(data)
